MONTH 4 — AI Intelligence Layer (April 2026)
---------------------------------------------
Week 13 — AI Sales Forecasting

This is a core thesis feature. The system forecasts
next 7 days of revenue per product based on historical
sales data. When actual sales fall below forecast,
a Critical Alert is triggered.

DB changes:
  CREATE TABLE ai_forecast (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    product_id INT REFERENCES products(id),
    forecast_date DATE NOT NULL,
    forecast_value NUMERIC NOT NULL,
    actual_value NUMERIC,
    accuracy NUMERIC,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
  );

  CREATE TABLE ai_recommendation (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    product_id INT REFERENCES products(id),
    product_name TEXT,
    recommendation TEXT,
    source_type TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
  );

  CREATE TABLE trending_keywords (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    keyword TEXT NOT NULL,
    rank_score NUMERIC,
    detected_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
  );

API endpoints:
- POST /api/forecasts/generate  ← runs forecast model
- GET  /api/forecasts            ← fetch predictions
- GET  /api/forecasts/alerts     ← products below threshold

Forecast model options (pick one):
- Simple: Linear regression on last 30 days of sales data
- Better: XGBoost via Python microservice (thesis mentions this)
- Simplest for demo: Moving average calculation in Node.js

Week 14 — Critical Alert + AI Recommendation

This is shown in the UI mockup as a dashboard modal.
When sales drop below forecast threshold, system:
  1. Detects the drop (scheduled check every hour via n8n)
  2. Shows Critical Sales Alert modal on dashboard
  3. Displays affected products + % drop
  4. Shows AI-generated recommendation text (OpenAI)
  5. Suggests: Generate Content / Create Campaign / View Analytics

Build:
- Dashboard alert modal (shown in Figure 3.12)
- AI recommendation text via OpenAI API
- Dismiss / act on alert behavior
- Store recommendation in ai_recommendation table

Week 15 — n8n Setup + Facebook Integration

⚠️ Apply for Facebook Developer App IMMEDIATELY
   Takes 1–2 weeks for approval.

n8n Workflow 1 — Auto Publisher (every 5 min):
  Poll GET /api/scheduled-posts/pending
  → For each pending post past scheduled_at:
    → POST to Facebook Graph API
    → On success: PATCH status to 'published' + save facebook_post_link
    → On failure: PATCH status to 'failed' + save error

n8n Workflow 2 — Engagement Collector (daily 9AM):
  → Fetch published posts from DB
  → Pull likes/comments/shares/reach from Facebook Graph API
  → Save to engagement_data table

n8n Workflow 3 — Sales Drop Detector (hourly):
  → Compare actual vs forecast sales
  → If below threshold: trigger AI recommendation
  → Store in ai_recommendation


